question: Is AZD9668 a VEGF mRNA drug?
ideal_answer: AZD9668 is a reversible and selective inhibitor of neutrophil elastase.

snippets.text: AZD9668, a neutrophil elastase inhibitor, plus ongoing budesonide/formoterol in patients with COPD.
AZD9668 is a reversible and selective inhibitor of NE, well tolerated at doses of 60 mg bid during Phase I/IIa development.
